    <note>Chang Gou [7118] Ancestors moved from Chang‘an to Tangyao at end of Tang. His great great great grandfather moved to Qiongzhou, Linqiong xian, where the Chang(2) became a great lineage (daxing). Gou failed in exams and did not take office. Lineage data in father's (Pu [3009]) funerary inscription. Anmin's [7000] father, Tong's [7001] grandfather, Teng(1) You(1)'s [7350] father-in-law. LvTao, WJ, 24.3b, 27.4b-6a (wife, born Li, who died in 1090 at age 52). Li(2) Xuan's [1033] family is another branch of this lineage established by the Tang Yantie pan-guan, Li(2) Gai [3511], who followed Xizong into Sichuan and settled in Qiongzhou, Yizheng xian. LvTao, WJ, 27.4b. CBD, 3, 2690.</note>
